<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/112867640-patrick-wichert"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/112867640-patrick-wichert">Patrick Wichert</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I think she either drowned in search of Excalibur or went away to wither and die, after failing to bring the gods back and reinstating Britain.<br/>As she <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I think she either drowned in search of Excalibur or went away to wither and die, after failing to bring the gods back and reinstating Britain.<br />As she becomes such an intense and driven character in this last book, I feel like she either would have died trying (and falling and we already know) to bring the old gods back or she would have lost hope after Camlann and would have retired to some forsaken place to await her end. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

