    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2938356240" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4705315303629916158">UGH<br/>I exclaim as I lovingly thwack the book down upon the table. These are too <i>fucking</i> good.<br/><br/>Excalibur is my favourite of the three. <b>I wasn’t bored once. </b><br/>This is how you write, lads.<br/>I endeavour to create like this. To captivate. Attention, emotions – reel them from a person like a fish on a line. Until they’re so intertwined, the distinctions between character and reader become irrelevant.<br/><br/>A perfect gathering of threads to close. Some tied up, others left dangling in the wind, leaving you to wonder</span>
  <span id="freeText4705315303629916158" style="display:none">UGH<br />I exclaim as I lovingly thwack the book down upon the table. These are too <i>fucking</i> good.<br /><br />Excalibur is my favourite of the three. <b>I wasn’t bored once. </b><br />This is how you write, lads.<br />I endeavour to create like this. To captivate. Attention, emotions – reel them from a person like a fish on a line. Until they’re so intertwined, the distinctions between character and reader become irrelevant.<br /><br />A perfect gathering of threads to close. Some tied up, others left dangling in the wind, leaving you to wonder. <br />And, this contains <b>the best sword fight I have ever read</b>. Never have I come across one more engrossing and <i>goddamn satisfying. </i> <br /><br /><br /><br />Initial Thoughts:<br />me, upon the conclusion of this book, holding it to my breast, smiling wistfully to myself, lying in a pool of tears of my own making, eyes closed: *sniffs* <br />*doesn’t move for a night and a day*</span>
  <a data-text-id="4705315303629916158" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

