<div id="review_2768030162" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2768030162" />
    <a title="Robert Sheard" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1863589-robert-sheard"><img alt="Robert Sheard" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1617235105p2/1863589.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2768030162?book_show_action=true">Dec 09, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Robert Sheard" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Robert Sheard" href="/user/show/1863589-robert-sheard">Robert Sheard</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781405928342" href="/book/show/30124185-excalibur">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2768030162" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10555097652241082321">I&apos;ve really enjoyed this series. It got off to a difficult start for me with all the names I didn&apos;t know, but Cornwell does such a good job of tying everything together. It&apos;s impressive how much this trilogy covered. It&apos;s not the tales of Arthur I grew up reading or hearing about, but a fascinating alternate version. </span>
  <span id="freeText10555097652241082321" style="display:none">I've really enjoyed this series. It got off to a difficult start for me with all the names I didn't know, but Cornwell does such a good job of tying everything together. It's impressive how much this trilogy covered. It's not the tales of Arthur I grew up reading or hearing about, but a fascinating alternate version. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10555097652241082321" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


